OL,3,GYorkshire & Humber
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FOutbreaks of rain becoming
OL,6,Fwidespread through the morning. These
OL,7,Feasing from the northwest, but could
OL,8,Fpersist into the evening across some
OL,9,Fsouthern areas. Turning breezy,
OL,10,Fespecially along the coast.
OL,11,
OL,12,CTonight:FDry and settled, with
OL,13,Fclearing skies overnight allowing
OL,14,Ftemperatures to fall and feeling cold.
OL,15,FWinds light but breezy along the coast.
OL,16,
OL,17,CSunday:FCold start Sunday, perhaps
OL,18,Ffrosty, then dry with sunny spells
OL,19,Fduring the morning before turning
OL,20,Fincreasingly cloudy by the afternoon.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
